This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) as it deals with the design and optimization of wireless sensor networks for health monitoring. It also involves the allocation of channels and scheduling of transmissions, which are key topics in network architecture. Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-categories of Information Theory (cs.IT) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) as it involves the optimization of wireless links and the control of network behavior. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as it deals with the security and reliability of wireless transmissions in health monitoring systems.
